title: Cross country; swimming; field hockey - Pewaukee Pirates' boys and girls cross country teams earn trip to state
text:
The Pewaukee boys and girls stormed into the state cross country meet Saturday.
The Pirates won sectional titles in a meet they hosted at the high school. Senior Robert Wagner and junior Kyle Turba finished 1-2 to lead the boys to a convincing win, while freshman Zoe Goodmanson finished third to lead the girls to a five-point victory over Whitewater.
The top two teams and the top five individuals who are not part of a qualifying team advance to the state meet, which will be run Saturday at Ridges Golf Course in Wisconsin Rapids.
Wagner completed the 5,000-meter course in 16 minutes 36.41 seconds. Turba completed the course in 16:47.10.
DIVISION 1 Homestead Sectional: Wauwatosa East senior Sam Potter (16:09.80) and Whitefish Bay junior Cami Davre (19:12.61) won individual titles.
The Bay girls took the top three spots at the meet run at Tendick Park. Junior Ellie Hall (19:32.09) and senior Claire Hentzen (20:00.88) were second and third.
Homestead's boys won the title. Freshman Drew Bosley finished second to Potter in 16:19.97. The Highlanders' top five were among the top 20 overall.
Mukwonago Sectional: Arrowhead's boys and girls were champions, though the girls race was much tighter. The Warhawks girls and Waukesha West each finished with 48 points, but Arrowhead got the top spot based on the finish of its sixth runner, junior Anna Hayes.
West senior Emma Langer won the girls race in 18:52.44. New Berlin Eisenhower's Matt Cavanaugh was the boys champion (16:19.29).
DIVISION 3 Lake Country Lutheran: Living Word Lutheran senior Andy Barnhart (16:58.84) and Kenosha St. Joseph senior Mady Scopp (19:42.02) won their races to lead their teams to sectional titles.
SWIMMING Classic 8 meet: Arrowhead brought home the team title and Muskego senior Katie Taylor set a conference record in the 100-yard backstroke with a time of 56.95 seconds. The old record of 57.10 was set by former Arrowhead standout Andrea Boritzke in 2004.
Senior Kelly Jacob and sophomore Abby Cabush were four-event winners for Arrowhead. Jacob took the 50 and 100 freestyle in 24.15 and 53.11 and was a part of the team's 200 medley and 200 freestyle relays. Cabush won the 200 free in 1:54.43 and the 100 butterfly in 58.20 and was a member of the 200 free and 400 free relays.
Mark Stewart
